flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Periodic inventory review and demand forecast update.]
  A --> N1[Stream: DDM/Crawlers - Retrieve current inventory levels and demand forecasts.]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Safety Stock Service - Calculate optimal safety stock levels.]
  N2 --> N3[Stream: STREAMS - Identify excess and obsolete inventory.]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process Builder - Develop deployment and rebalancing strategies.}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[Cortex: Remote Functions - Evaluate working capital impact.]
  N5 --> N6[PB: CWB Lifecycle - Present recommendations for approval.]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced working capital and COGS with maintained or improved service levels and OTIF.]
  N4 -->|Excess inventory exceeds threshold.| B1[Trigger additional mitigation strategies.]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Further reduce excess inventory through targeted actions.]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Service level requirements not met.| B2[Adjust safety stock levels and re-evaluate.]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Ensure service levels are maintained while optimizing inventory.]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Working capital impact exceeds budget.| B3[Re-optimize inventory strategies.]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Balance working capital constraints with service level requirements.]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]